'''Jeff Carlisle''' is an illustrator and concept artist from the United States, working primarily in gaming.

==Biography==
Carlisle' contributions to ''[[Star Wars]]'' include ''[[The New Jedi Order Sourcebook]]'', the ''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]'', the [[Starships of the Galaxy (Saga Edition)|''Starships of the Galaxy'' (Saga Edition)]], ''[[Threats of the Galaxy]]'' and ''[[Galaxy at War]]'' for the [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game|Star Wars Role-Playing Game]], as well as designs for the ''[[Star Wars Miniatures]]'' game. He has also done hundreds of hand-drawn sketch card illustrations for the Star Wars Heritage and Revenge of the Sith card sets from [[The Topps Company, Inc.|Topps]]. Carlisle was one of the artists who worked on [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (webcomics)|''The Clone Wars'' web comics]].

Carlisle is well known for his starship designs. For a time he did nearly all the starship designs in ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' and ''[[Polyhedron]]'' magazines and notably designed the [[Nssis-class Clawcraft|Clawcraft]]. He also contributed designs and illustrations of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] for the magazine and designed the ''[[No Luck Required]]'' for the short story ''[[Emissary of the Void]]''.

Carlisle was one of the contributing illustrators for [[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']], contributing two color plates and new starship designs.

He was a regular contributor to [[Wikipedia:Dungeon (magazine)|''Dungeon'']] and [[Wikipedia:Dragon (magazine)|''Dragon'']] magazines for the last five years of their print run and contributed concept designs and illustrations for tabletop games, collectible card games and at least one [[Wikipedia:Whacked!|video game]].

He was featured as an artist at Star Wars Celebrations [[Celebration II|II]], [[Celebration IV|IV]] and [[Celebration V|V]].

Carlisle is a member of [[Star Wars Artists Guild]].

